abstract: While the overall U.S. response to climate change is up to elected officials, Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell said on Wednesday, the Fed can play a part in keeping global warming from destabilising U.S. banks and financial markets.
snippet: While the overall U.S. response to climate change is up to elected officials, Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell said on Wednesday, the Fed can play a part in keeping global warming from destabilising U.S. banks and financial markets.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — While the overall U.S. response to climate change is up to elected officials, Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell said on Wednesday, the Fed can play a part in keeping global warming from destabilising U.S. banks and financial markets.
headline_main: Fed Has a Role in Combating Climate Change Risk, Powell Says
headline_print_headline: Fed Has a Role in Combating Climate Change Risk, Powell Says

abstract: Knowing that they may not hear from new witnesses, senators may home in what outstanding information still exists.
snippet: Knowing that they may not hear from new witnesses, senators may home in what outstanding information still exists.
lead_paragraph: Senator Chuck Schumer of New York, the minority leader, expressed doubts on Wednesday that he would be able to secure the votes to introduce new witnesses in the trial. At the same time, Democratic and Republic senators alike began tailoring their questions to effectively turn the members of each legal team into witnesses themselves.
headline_main: What to watch: How will questions shift as the prospect of witnesses fades?

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg will use his Super Bowl ad to highlight his efforts to combat gun violence, while President Donald Trump will focus on his economic record as the two candidates face off during the year's most-watched television event.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg will use his Super Bowl ad to highlight his efforts to combat gun violence, while President Donald Trump will focus on his economic record as the two candidates face off during the year's most-wa...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg will use his Super Bowl ad to highlight his efforts to combat gun violence, while President Donald Trump will focus on his economic record as the two candidates face off during the year's most-watched television event.
headline_main: Bloomberg, Trump Detail Campaign Ads to Air on Super Bowl
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg, Trump Detail Campaign Ads to Air on Super Bowl

abstract: The Rev. Raphael Warnock, pastor of the Atlanta church where the Rev. Martin Luther King Jr. preached, announced Thursday he's running for U.S. Senate, challenging recently appointed Republican Sen. Kelly Loeffler.
snippet: The Rev. Raphael Warnock, pastor of the Atlanta church where the Rev. Martin Luther King Jr. preached, announced Thursday he's running for U.S. Senate, challenging recently appointed Republican Sen. Kelly Loeffler.
lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — The Rev. Raphael Warnock, pastor of the Atlanta church where the Rev. Martin Luther King Jr. preached, announced Thursday he's running for U.S. Senate, challenging recently appointed Republican Sen. Kelly Loeffler.
headline_main: Ebenezer Pastor Raphael Warnock Enters US Senate Race
headline_print_headline: Ebenezer Pastor Raphael Warnock Enters US Senate Race

abstract: The U.S.-Mexico-Canada trade agreement (USMCA) signed by  President Donald Trump on Wednesday modernizes the 26-year-old North American Free Trade Agreement, which has been blamed for  hollowing out the U.S. manufacturing sector.
snippet: The U.S.-Mexico-Canada trade agreement (USMCA) signed by  President Donald Trump on Wednesday modernizes the 26-year-old North American Free Trade Agreement, which has been blamed for  hollowing out the U.S. manufacturing sector.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - The U.S.-Mexico-Canada trade agreement (USMCA) signed by President Donald Trump on Wednesday modernizes the 26-year-old North American Free Trade Agreement, which has been blamed for hollowing out the U.S. manufacturing sector.
headline_main: Factbox: How the North American Trade Deal Will Affect Autos, Digital Trade, Drugs
headline_print_headline: Factbox: How the North American Trade Deal Will Affect Autos, Digital Trade, Drugs

abstract: Michael R. Bloomberg’s campaign will air a 60-second ad promoting his record on gun control, while President Trump has lined up a commercial celebrating his time in office.
snippet: Michael R. Bloomberg’s campaign will air a 60-second ad promoting his record on gun control, while President Trump has lined up a commercial celebrating his time in office.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Two billionaires will pitch their presidential candidacies amid the beer and car commercials of the Super Bowl on Sunday, with Michael R. Bloomberg spending a full minute addressing gun violence and President Trump using 30 seconds to highlight his first years in office.

abstract: In his first address to the U.S. Congress, President Donald Trump hailed General Motors Co, Harley-Davidson Inc, Intel Corp and seven other companies as innovators and job creators, predicting they would be among those producing "tens of thousands of new American jobs" and investing "billions and billions of dollars."

abstract: The White House is considering further restrictions on U.S. airlines flying to and from China in addition to voluntary restrictions that the companies have put into place, President Donald Trump's economic adviser Larry Kudlow said on Wednesday.
snippet: The White House is considering further restrictions on U.S. airlines flying to and from China in addition to voluntary restrictions that the companies have put into place, President Donald Trump's economic adviser Larry Kudlow said on Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The White House is considering further restrictions on U.S. airlines flying to and from China in addition to voluntary restrictions that the companies have put into place, President Donald Trump's economic adviser Larry Kudlow said on Wednesday.
headline_main: Restrictions for Airlines Flying to China Under Discussion-White House's Kudlow
headline_print_headline: Restrictions for Airlines Flying to China Under Discussion-White House's Kudlow

abstract: Global airlines on Wednesday suspended or scaled back more direct flights to China's major cities amid an increase in travel warnings and decline in demand from passengers due to a growing outbreak of coronavirus.    Fears over the spread of the flu-like virus, which originated in the central Chinese city of Wuhan, are increasing as the death toll topped 160.
snippet: Global airlines on Wednesday suspended or scaled back more direct flights to China's major cities amid an increase in travel warnings and decline in demand from passengers due to a growing outbreak of coronavirus.    Fears over the spread of the f...
lead_paragraph: LONDON/MONTREAL — Global airlines on Wednesday suspended or scaled back more direct flights to China's major cities amid an increase in travel warnings and decline in demand from passengers due to a growing outbreak of coronavirus. Fears over the spread of the flu-like virus, which originated in the central Chinese city of Wuhan, are increasing as the death toll topped 160.
headline_main: Airlines Suspend, Scale Back Direct Flights to China Amid Virus Fears
headline_print_headline: Airlines Suspend, Scale Back Direct Flights to China Amid Virus Fears

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg has won the backing of Equality California, one of the nation's largest LGBTQ membership organizations, and its Nevada partner organization, an endorsement that could give him a boost in critical Western primaries.
